.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-LOG" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-log \- fetch recent CLN log entries
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-log
.RB [ --level
.IR io | debug | info | unusual | broken ]
.RB [ --limit
.IR N ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Fetches the recent CLN daemon log buffer via
.BR lightning-cli (1)
.BR getlog .
Returns a JSON array of log entries:
.nf
[{"time":"...","source":"...","log":"...","level":"..."}]
.fi
Entries are returned in chronological order.
.TP
.B --level io|debug|info|unusual|broken
Minimum log level to include (default: info).
.TP
.B --limit N
Return the last N entries (default 50, max 1000).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success (returns empty array if daemon unavailable).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-node-info (1)
